disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Blast Shield.

blurb.value: Vi charges a shield over time. The shield can be activated by hitting an enemy with an ability.

description.value: Innate: Hitting an enemy with an ability grants Vi a shield equal to  15% of her maximum health for 3 seconds.

description2.value: Blast Shield's  cooldown is reduced by 3 seconds for every trigger of Denting Blows.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

notes.value: * Triggering Denting Blows will not activate Blast Shield.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Vault Breaker.

blurb.value: Vi charges her gauntlets and unleashes a vault shattering punch, carrying her forward. Enemies she hits are knocked back and receive a stack of Denting Blows.

description.value: Active: Vi charges for up to 4 seconds to increase Vault Breaker's  range, speed, and damage while being slowed by 15%. Vault Breaker can be recast at any time within its duration.

description2.value: If the charge completes without reactivation, Vault Breaker is canceled and goes on full cooldown.

description3.value: Recast: Vi dashes in the target direction, dealing physical damage to all enemies she passes through, increased by 0% − 100% (based on channel time).

leveling3.value: Minimum Physical Damage:»55 / 80 / 105 / 130 / 155 (+ 70% bonus AD)«Maximum Damage:110 / 160 / 210 / 260 / 310 (+ 140% bonus AD)

description4.value: Vi stops upon colliding with an enemy champion, knocking them back while non-champion enemies in her path are instead pulled towards her.

description5.value: Vault Breaker will go on a 3-second  cooldown if the charge is canceled.

Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Denting Blows.

blurb.value: Vi's punches break her opponent's Armor, dealing bonus damage and granting her Attack Speed.

description.value: Passive: Vi's basic attacks on-hit and Vault Breaker apply Denting Blows to enemies hit, stacking up to 3 times. At 3 stacks, Vi consumes them to deal bonus physical damage and  reduce the target's armor by 20%, with the bonus damage capped at 300 against non-champions.

leveling.value: Bonus Physical Damage:4 / 5.5 / 7 / 8.5 / 10% (+「 1% per 35 」「 2.86% per 100 」bonus AD) of target's maximum health

description2.value: After triggering Denting Blows, Vi gains  bonus attack speed for 4 seconds, refreshing on subsequent triggers.

description3.value: The debuff is applied after the damage has been dealt.

blurb.value: Vi's next attack blasts through her target, dealing damage to enemies behind it.

description3.value: Excessive Force resets Vi's basic attack timer.

disp_name.description:
Name of the ability
Only necessary if the value differs from Assault and Battery.

target range.value: 800

blurb.value: Vi runs down an enemy, knocking aside anyone in the way. When she reaches her target she knocks it into the air, jumps after it, and slams it back into the ground.

description.value: Active: Vi reveals the target enemy champion and dashes with displacement immunity towards them, dealing physical damage and knocking them up for 1.25 seconds upon arrival.

description2.value: Enemies along the way are dealt the same damage, knocked aside by 350 units over 0.25 seconds, and simultaneously stunned for 0.75 seconds.

targeting.description: Permafrost is a single target ability.

affects.description: Permafrost affects enemy champions and large monsters

onhiteffects.description: onhiteffects can be set to 'true', for abilities that apply on-hit effects (from items or other abilities)

occurrence.description: occurrence can either be set to 'hit' or 'attack', and refers to on-hit effects

spellshield.description: spellshield can either be set to true, or written with a custom description.

callforhelp.description: callforhelp determines whether minion aggro will transfer to the caster

additional.description: Displays additional information in a smaller window below the template.

notes.value: * Vi can cast Flash to reposition herself during the dash without ending the dash prematurely. Vi is unstoppable while knocking up her primary target but loses it afterwards. She cannot cast Flash during this part of the ability. While charging, Vi's dash speed ramps up overtime to ensure the target cannot escape. Vi will track targets that change locations (e.g. by moving, blinking, dashing, or being displaced). Assault and Battery has a maximum tether range, meaning it does not extensively follow targets that blink too far away (e.g. Teleport, Recall). If the target blinks to a far distance while Vi is dashing, she will stop prematurely but maintain the unstoppability for 7 seconds.* If the target becomes untargetable, is too far away, or dies during Assault and Battery's cast time, the ability will cancel. Assault and Battery does not go on  cooldown nor consume  mana in any of these cases. However, if Vi is dashing and the target becomes untargetable, she loses her unstoppability, stops dashing, and instead walks towards the target forcefully. If she comes into contact with the target, she will apply the airborne effect but no damage is dealt. If Vi goes into resurrection during Assault and Battery's cast time she will still initiate the dash and apply the knock up to her target but no damage is dealt. If Vi however enters resurrection during the dash, she will stop, but will keep the unstoppability for another 3 seconds after reviving. Vi will apply the knock up and damage even if she dies while being in range of her target.
